<title>USA: AlliedSignal opens plant in China.</title>
<headline>AlliedSignal opens plant in China.</headline>
<dateline>MORRIS TOWNSHIP, N.J. 1996-10-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>AlliedSignal Inc said Thursday it had opened a plant in China to manufacture amorphous metal cores for utility and industrial transformers.</p>
<p>The company said the transformers have the potential to &quot;significantly&quot; reduce China's energy consumption by lowering the energy lost from transformer cores.</p>
<p>The plant, in Shanghai, employs about 20 people and has the capacity to produce 450 tons of amorphous metal cores each year, the company said.</p>
<p>AlliedSignal said it is in the process of tripling that capacity.</p>
